        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(api): guard moderated skill files and tags",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nHardens public skill artifact and latest-version readers so moderated or stale data cannot leak through alternate public paths.\n\n## What changed\n\n- Public skill file readers now share the same moderation block semantics as ZIP downloads.\n- Skill tags must point at a non-deleted version that belongs to the same skill.\n- Digest-backed public lists fail closed unless the denormalized latest-version owner marker matches the skill.\n- Review follow-up: `getBySlug` and `resolveVersionByHash` now also suppress stale, cross-skill, or soft-deleted latest-version docs instead of serializing them.\n- Preserves the digest/backfill validation model; expensive validation stays out of hot public list paths.\n\n## Behavior proof\n\nFocused regressions now exercise the real public-reader boundaries:\n\n- `getBySlug` returns the skill while omitting a soft-deleted `latestVersion`.\n- `resolveVersionByHash` omits `latestVersion` when the latest row is soft-deleted.\n- `resolveVersionByHash` omits `latestVersion` when the latest row belongs to another skill.\n- Public file/API/tag tests still cover moderated artifact blocks and cross-skill tag rejection.\n\nThe corrected public contract is: invalid latest-version state becomes `null`/absent, never a serialized stale version object.\n\n## Validation\n\n```text\n$ bun run test convex/skills.public.test.ts convex/httpApiV1.handlers.test.ts convex/downloads.test.ts convex/skills.deleteTags.test.ts convex/skills.publicListCursor.test.ts convex/lib/skillSearchDigest.test.ts\nTest Files  6 passed (6)\nTests       252 passed (252)\n```\n\n```text\n$ bun run ci:static\npassed\n```\n\n```text\n$ bun run ci:unit\nTest Files  204 passed (204)\nTests       2003 passed (2003)\nStatements  85.98%\nBranches    75.17%\nFunctions   86.37%\nLines        89.48%\n```\n\n```text\n$ bun run ci:types-build\ntsc, package typechecks, clawhub-mod typecheck, Vite build, and Nitro build passed.\n```\n\n## External blocker\n\nThe known Vercel preview failure is team authorization required for deployment. That is maintainer-owned and not a patch failure.\n\nAI-assisted: yes. I reviewed the diff, can maintain it, and validated it with the commands above.\n",
